The sequel to Sierra's award-winning NASCAR Racing, NASCAR 2 used a new game engine, which improved the graphics, physics, sound, and multiplayer.

It also added the official cars, tracks, and drivers of the 1996 season, an arcade mode, mouse interface, and radio spotter.

It was also the first NASCAR game to use have 3D Acceleration 3Dfx Acceleration through DOS, and Rendition through Windows.